Adding a "Clear Form" button to your EcoLens application is actually quite straightforward! It requires minimal work since you already have the resetForm() method implemented. Here's what you need to add:

1. Add the Button in the Record Panel HTML

Add this button to your Record panel, right after the existing "Record Observation" button:

```html
<!-- Inside the record-panel, after the Record Observation button -->
<button id="record-btn" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" aria-label="Record observation">
    <i class="fas fa-save" aria-hidden="true"></i> Record Observation
</button>

<!-- ADD THIS BUTTON -->
<button id="clear-form-btn" class="btn btn-outline btn-block" aria-label="Clear form">
    <i class="fas fa-eraser" aria-hidden="true"></i> Clear Form
</button>
```

2. Add the Event Listener in JavaScript

Add this event listener in the setupEventListeners() method (around line 1700):

```javascript
// Clear form button
const clearFormBtn = document.getElementById('clear-form-btn');
if (clearFormBtn) {
    clearFormBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (confirm('Are you sure you want to clear the form? All entered data will be lost.')) {
            this.resetForm();
            this.showStatus('Form cleared', 'info');
        }
    });
}
```

Alternative: More Prominent Placement

If you want the button to be more visible, you could place it in the button group with the Record button:

```html
<!-- Replace the single Record button with a button group -->
<div class="btn-group" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <button id="record-btn" class="btn btn-primary" aria-label="Record observation">
        <i class="fas fa-save" aria-hidden="true"></i> Record Observation
    </button>
    <button id="clear-form-btn" class="btn btn-outline" aria-label="Clear form">
        <i class="fas fa-eraser" aria-hidden="true"></i> Clear Form
    </button>
</div>
```

Optional: Keyboard Shortcut

You could also add a keyboard shortcut (Ctrl+Shift+C or similar):

```javascript
// Add keyboard shortcut for clearing form
document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    // Ctrl+Shift+C to clear form (when not in input field)
    if (e.ctrlKey && e.shiftKey && e.key === 'C' && 
        !['INPUT', 'TEXTAREA', 'SELECT'].includes(document.activeElement.tagName)) {
        e.preventDefault();
        const clearBtn = document.getElementById('clear-form-btn');
        if (clearBtn) clearBtn.click();
    }
});
```

Summary of Changes:

1. Add HTML button - 1 line in the Record panel
2. Add JavaScript event listener - 5-7 lines in setupEventListeners()
3. (Optional) Style adjustments if needed

Estimated time: 5-10 minutes to implement and test.

The resetForm() method already handles all the form clearing logic, so you're just adding a button to trigger it with a confirmation dialog for safety. This is a very low-effort, high-usability addition to your application!
